<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-640-078  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 640 078.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>CommunicationsWeek  July 16 1990 n309 p2(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC eyes int'l links.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Killette, Kathleen.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The US Federal Communications Commission (FCC) is proposing toease the cost burden of telephone companies that provideinternational service by implementing a cost-based accountingstructure.andP;  The proposal will give US carriers more negotiatingpower for accounting rates with their foreign counterparts.andP;  Thenew accounting system should reduce the payments US carriers maketo foreign carriers, which has soared from $78 million in 1975 to$1.6 billion in 1988.andP;  The FCC reported that US carriers paidforeign postal telephone and telegraph (PTT) authorities $2billion in 1988 to settle accounts for international services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     United States. Federal Communications CommissionFiber OpticsTelecommunicationsInternational CommunicationsTelephone Companies.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>